A_{2 \times 2} = U \begin{bmatrix}\Sigma_{11} & 0\\ 0 & \Sigma_{22} \end{bmatrix}V^*
A^{-1} = V^{*^{-1}} \begin{bmatrix}\dfrac1{\Sigma_{11}} & 0\\ 0 & \dfrac1{\Sigma_{22}} \end{bmatrix} U^{-1}
\det(A) = 1
\Sigma_{11} \Sigma_{22} = 1
\Vert B \Vert_2 = \max \{\sigma_i: \sigma_i \text{ is a singular value of }B\}
\Vert A \Vert_2 = \Sigma_{11}
\Vert A^{-1} \Vert_2 = \dfrac1{\Sigma_{22}} = \Sigma_{11}
\Vert A \Vert_2 = \Vert A^{-1} \Vert_2
\left \Vert A \right \Vert_{F} = \sqrt{\Sigma_{11}^2 + \dfrac1{\Sigma_{11}^2}} = \left \Vert A^{-1} \right \Vert_F
